   <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/014053.html"><b>Stopping
    Camping</b></a><br>
    <font color="#FF0000">[Quote from original post: Most groups finally leave
    in frustration to find a more productive hunting spot as their exp bar
    stagnates.]<br>
    </font><br>
    Thats an idea, of course Id rather try to encourage people to go elsewhere
    rather than frustrating them until they do :) Overall I agree with the
    intent of your suggestion if not its implementation exactly.<br>
    <br>
    A common suggestion here on the boards is, &quot;As more people enter a
    zone, more creatures shoudl spawn and more loot should be dropped&quot;.
    That suggestion is often labeled the &quot;cure for camping&quot;.
    Unfortunately, increasing the supply due to increasing demand only
    encourages more demand.<br>
    <br>
    In other words, if Oasis is crowded now with 80 people, imagine how crowded
    it would be if there was enough creatures to support however many people
    wanted to pile into the zone. As it is, we hope that someone walks into
    oasis, sees 80 people, says, &quot;man, this is crowded&quot;, and goes
    someplace else.<br>
    <br>
   <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/014031.html"><b>&quot;@&quot;
